<h2>The Question</h2>
<p>
    <a href="/backlog/747-design-system-equals-theme-plus-intents-bundle-manifest-catalog/">#747</a>
    ratified <em>what a design system is</em> — a config-flavor manifest
    (<code>{ extends, themeTokens, intentDefaults?, traitDefaults? }</code>).
    <a href="/backlog/775-design-system-creator-assembler-open-core-layering-simple-fu/">#775</a> must
    settle the <strong>open-core tiering of the tool that authors it</strong>: a <em>simple</em> assembler
    embedded natively in FUI (free) and the <em>full</em> creator offered as a Plateau product
    (<a href="/backlog/751-embedded-theme-design-system-creator-plateau/">#751</a>, the upsell). The
    two-tier split is settled by construction (<a href="/backlog/091-web-docs-as-a-service-plateau/">#091</a>'s
    constellation decomposition); the open question is <strong>exactly where the free/paid line sits — which
    knobs are free</strong>. This survey gathers how comparable design-system / token / theme-builder tools
    draw that line, per design-first step&nbsp;1, so the call reuses the market's vocabulary rather than
    coining a tiering cold.
</p>

<h2>Recommendation (forks in #775)</h2>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Partitioning principle = the capability-cost line.</strong> Free = any deterministic,
        fixed-cost, locally-runnable authoring that produces a self-hostable #747 manifest; paid = variable
        per-call cost (vision/AI) <em>or</em> hosted persistence / collaboration / managed-vendor
        integration. This is the market's universal line <em>and</em> the composition of #091 (self-host
        floor), <a href="/backlog/475-design-ref-vision-gated-capture-qc-candidate-surface-quality/">#475</a> +
        the linear-cost rule (no uncapped per-call cost in the free floor), and minimize-lock-in (the free
        floor speaks the open format). <em>High confidence — a composition of existing rulings, not a new
        judgment.</em></li>
    <li><strong>DTCG import free; proprietary-Figma ingest paid.</strong> The free FUI floor imports
        <strong>DTCG</strong> (the open standard #747 already references — free everywhere in the market);
        <strong>Figma ingest is a paid Plateau capability</strong> (a managed proprietary-vendor integration
        needing API auth — the canonical Tokens&nbsp;Studio Pro line). <em>Med-high confidence.</em></li>
</ol>

