<h2>Finding 2 — the line is tri-partite, and every tool agrees on all three</h2>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Manual, deterministic, locally-runnable authoring → FREE.</strong> Pick/edit tokens, set
        values, export to a standard format. Material Theme Builder gates nothing here; Tokens Studio's free
        tier <em>is</em> this.</li>
    <li><strong>Per-call variable-cost automation (AI/vision) → PAID, metered.</strong> Screenshot→theme and
        AI generation are always metered per-call (Codia's $49/image). No tool offers unbounded AI on a flat
        free tier.</li>
    <li><strong>Managed integration + hosted persistence + collaboration → PAID.</strong> Figma-Styles sync,
        multi-file/branching, cloud save, sharing, team/governance — the Tokens Studio Pro line and the whole
        of the zeroheight/Supernova/Knapsack paid tiers.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Finding 3 — open-standard import is free; proprietary-vendor integration is paid</h2>
<p>
    The split inside "import" is instructive: <strong>DTCG import is free everywhere</strong> (Material Theme
    Builder imports DTCG/DSP free; Style Dictionary is OSS) — it is parsing an open standard you already own.
    <strong>Figma-Styles connection is the canonical Pro feature</strong> in Tokens Studio — a proprietary
    vendor <em>managed integration</em> needing API auth, not a file parse. So the free/paid line inside
    ingest runs along <strong>open-standard format (free) vs proprietary-vendor managed integration
    (paid)</strong> — not "any import = paid."
</p>

<h2>Finding 4 — mapped onto WE's rulings, the line is almost entirely <em>forced</em></h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>The two-tier split is forced by #091</strong> — FUI ships the free self-host floor; the
        complete product is a plateau-app open-core offering. A free FUI-native assembler + a full Plateau
        creator (#751) <em>is</em> that pattern, not a fork.</li>
    <li><strong>Manual authoring must be free</strong> — the #747 manifest is a WE <em>standard</em> artifact;
        hand-authoring it must be in the free tier or the self-host promise breaks (#751 already frames it as
        localStorage, no sign-in).</li>
    <li><strong>Vision/screenshot→theme is forced PAID</strong> by
        <a href="/backlog/475-design-ref-vision-gated-capture-qc-candidate-surface-quality/">#475</a>
        (vision is a no-leakage Plateau service, never a WE capability) + the linear-cost rule (no uncapped
        per-call cost in the free floor) — confirmed by the universally-metered market.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud persist/share/collaboration is forced PAID</strong> by #751's sign-in-to-persist upsell
        and the universal market line.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Three of the four boundary segments are forced. The only genuinely-open call is the <em>principle</em>
    governing future knobs (Fork 1) and the one knob it most contests — deterministic format import,
    DTCG&nbsp;vs proprietary Figma (Fork 2).
</p>

